Officials have blamed conflict between legally operating taxis and those without permits for the violent protests. CAPE TOWN - Prince George Drive had been closed due to protests in Vrygrond.Officials have blamed conflict between legally operating taxis and those without permits for the violent protests.Authorities have rolled out an aggressive enforcement campaign to rid the area of illegal taxi operators over the past few weeks.Earlier City Traffic Spokesperson Maxine Bezuidenhout said: Reports of unrest in the Capricorn area and as result, Prince George Drive has been closed at Vrygrond avenue. Motorists are being diverted by officials on the scene. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)